Freight
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for delivery, shipping, or shipping and handling. these charges represent the cost of the transportation of product sold to the customer, and if applicable, any special charges for handling or preparing the product for shipping. these separately identified charges are paid to the seller of the goods and not to the shipping company.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Delivery by company vehicle
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Transportation charges imposed by the seller of the product for delivery of sold products using a company vehicle rather through a third party delivery service.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Delivery by company vehicle before passage of title
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Transportation charges imposed by the seller of the product for delivery of sold product using a company vehicle rather through a third-party delivery service. the transfer of title to the customer does not take place until after the customer takes possession of the product (fob destination).

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Delivery by company vehicle after passage of title
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Transportation charges imposed by the seller of the product for delivery of sold product using a company vehicle rather than through a third-party delivery service. the transfer of title to the customer takes place prior to the delivery of the product (fob origin).

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping only (not paid directly to common carrier)
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for shipping of product through a third-party common carrier paid to the seller. the charges represents the cost of transportation "only" without any additional charges for handling.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping only common carrier - fob destination (backward compatibility)
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for delivery of product through a third-party common carrier paid to the seller where the title to the product is transferred at the time the customer takes possession of the goods.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping only common carrier - fob destination
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for delivery of product through a third-party common carrier paid to the seller where the title to the product is transferred at the time the customer takes possession of the goods.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping only common carrier - fob origin
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for delivery of product through a third-party common carrier paid to the seller where the title to the product is transferred at the time of sales and prior to shipment.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping only non-common carrier - fob destination
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for delivery of product through a third-party non-common carrier paid to the seller where the title to the product is transferred at the time the customer takes possession of the goods.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping only non-common carrier - fob origin
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for delivery of product through a third-party non-common carrier paid to the seller where the title to the product is transferred at the time of sales and prior to shipment.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping charges that exceed the actual cost of delivery
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for shipping "only" that exceeds the actual cost of transporting the product to the customer.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Shipping charges that exceed reasonable and prevailing rates
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Charges for shipping "only" that exceeds what is deemed to be "reasonable" and "prevailing" rates.

AvaTax System Tax Code Description: Tangible personal property (tpp)
Additional AvaTax System Tax Code Inform: Tangible personal property is generally deemed to be items, other than real property (i.e. land and buildings etc.), that are tangible in nature. the presumption of taxability is on all items of tpp unless specifically made non-taxable by individual state and/or local statutes. this system tax code can be used when no other specific system tax code is applicable or available. additionally, this system tax code has a taxable default associated with it and consequently the user could use this code for any and all products that are known to be taxable and if they want to limit the number of system tax codes being used.
